sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT patient_id) AS number_of_abnormal_patients
FROM vital_signs
WHERE abnormality_flag = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Health indicators include heart rate, pulse, respiratory rate, blood oxygen saturation, blood pressure, and body temperature.
- Standard norms for these indicators can vary, but typical ranges are considered for heart rate (60-100 bpm), pulse (60-100 bpm), respiratory rate (12-20 breaths per minute), blood oxygen saturation (90-100%), systolic blood pressure (90-130 mmHg), diastolic blood pressure (60-80 mmHg), and body temperature (36 to 38 degrees Celsius).;
- "Out of the ordinary" refers to a condition where an individual's vital signs frequently exceed or fall short of these standard norms.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT m.patient_id) AS total_patients
FROM medications m
JOIN diagnoses d ON m.patient_id = d.patient_id;
